The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 The board of Alembic Ltd will meet on November 14 to consider the proposal of buying back equity shares from the open market. After the announcement, shares of the company surged 16.5 per cent to touch an intra-day high of Rs 36 on the BSE before closing at Rs 34.70, up 12.30 per cent from yesterdays close .                            
	 Bata India has reported a 30 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 12.40 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2008. The turnover stood at Rs 232.53 crore, a 13 per cent increase over the same quarter of the previous fiscal.                             
	 Visa Steel has posted a 482 per cent increase in profit after tax for the second quarter of 2008-09 at Rs 20.10 crore. The companys revenue grew 115 per cent to Rs 331.14 crore.                             
	 Simplex Infrastructures has reported a 47 per cent rise in net profit for the second quarter of 2008-09 at Rs 28 crore against Rs 19 crore in the year-ago period.                             
	 The total income of IFGL Refractories has increased 40.82 per cent to Rs 126.09 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2008, from Rs 89.54 crore in the same quarter last year.                             
	 Graphite India has registered a 45 per cent rise in sale and income from operation at Rs 403.33 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2008, , against Rs 277.99 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year.                             
	 Vodafone Essar has opened four stores in Calcutta, Siuri and Krishnanagar.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
